    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This looks wonderful. I, too, started making granola.  I put dried cherries in mine, and use a mix of honey and maple syrup as the sweetener.  I haven&#39;t used oil in mine, but if I did, olive would be the way to go! </p>
<p>The recipe, should you wish to check it out, is here:</p>
<p><a href="http://eggton.com/2011/11/19/black-cherry-granola/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://eggton.com/2011/11/19/black-cherry-granola/</a></p>
<p>So glad you posted this. Granola is such a lovely way to start the morning.  Cheers!</p>
