    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I think it&#39;s hilarious that you concede that you don&#39;t travel with your own granola YET.</p>
<p>That reminded me of the time my hippie aunt and uncle came to visit us when we still lived in Florida. They literally brought the granola and ALL possible mix-ins in blue ball jars and lined them all up on our kitchen counter. Every day they stayed with us they opened jars and concocted what seemed like potions. I can&#39;t imagine trying to pack 20 jars for a flight these days.</p>
    </div>

