  <li id="comment-35446" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/i-am-here-to-tell-you/#comment-35446"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-01-27T18:55:03-05:00">Friday, January 27, 2012 at 6:55 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I saw this on Food52 and considered making it &#8211; will have to try.  But it is hard to stray from my all-time favorite granola, which is unusual in that the only fat is in the form of a bit of butter streusel that you mix in before adding sweetener.  And it&#39;s not at all heavy with only 1/3 cup maple syrup, 2Tbsp sugar, and 2 Tbsp butter for 5 cups of grains/nuts.  It also has the texture you mentioned &#8211; clumpy, yet crunchy and really tasty.  If you or anyone else is interested&#8230;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.foodandwine.com/recipes/almond-maple-granola" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.foodandwine.com/recipes/almond-maple-granola</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-35446' data-commentid="35446" data-postid="439" data-belowelement="comment-35446" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
