  <li id="comment-35591" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/15419619001984506774" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Unknown</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/i-am-here-to-tell-you/#comment-35591"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-01-30T23:53:26-05:00">Monday, January 30, 2012 at 11:53 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>So, I screwed up while making this but that&#39;s OK! I accidentally bought sweetened coconut instead of regular and therefore only put half the amount in. But the best part is where I left it cooling in a slab &#8211; my usual granola recipe does this to get some crumbly clumps &#8211; and it became a rather solid mass. <br />Well, they&#39;re the best granola bars I&#39;ve ever made.</p>
    </div>

