  <li id="comment-35647" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/i-am-here-to-tell-you/#comment-35647"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-07-11T22:22:36-04:00">Friday, July 11, 2014 at 10:22 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have made a similar delicious granola for years but never with olive oil.  That is a great tip.  I also use a mix of rolled oats, barley and rye.  All really heart healthy and add a complexity to just rolled oats.  I do the same thing when I cook rolled oats for hot cereal.  A batch of granola is in the oven now with olive oil.  Thanks!</p>
    </div>

