  <li id="comment-53832" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">MeKayla Woodward</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/i-am-here-to-tell-you/#comment-53832"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-05-12T21:27:36-04:00">Thursday, May 12, 2016 at 9:27 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This is seriously my new fave go-to granola recipe! I&#8217;ve made it three times now and love the saltiness. Once before, I ran out of maple syrup so I subbed in some honey and it was equally as delicious. I love eating it with goat yogurt. Thanks so much!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-53832' data-commentid="53832" data-postid="439" data-belowelement="comment-53832" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to MeKayla Woodward" aria-label='Reply to MeKayla Woodward'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-74366" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Caroline Scott</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/i-am-here-to-tell-you/#comment-74366"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2019-08-07T12:59:24-04:00">Wednesday, August 7, 2019 at 12:59 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I make a similar granola (recipe from New York Times recipe from Eleven Madison Park Restaurant in NYC; however, I use 3 cups organic rolled oats, 1/3 cup brown sugar, 1/3 cup Mediterranean Blend Olive Oil, 1/3 cup maple syrup, 1 cup raw pistachios, 1 cup raw pumpkin seeds, 1-1/2 cup organic coconut shards (from Trader Joe&#8217;s),  1 cup raw almonds,  1 cup dried, chopped cherries, 1 cup dried, chopped apricots.  I get rave reviews from friends fortunate enough to eat some that I bring to work or those that order from me!</p>
         
  
